The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Aug. 11: A group of drunk youths blocked Justice Pronab Chattopadhyays car in the Bowbazar area this evening and allegedly slapped his driver. 

 A traffic sergeant intervened to prevent the situation from turning worse and the chauffeur drove to the Bowbazar police station, the judge sitting inside. Four people have been detained. Witnesses said before targeting the VIP car, the gang had set upon two autorickshaws near the Colootala Street-Central Avenue intersection.

 Calcutta: A Siliguri resident has challenged in the high court the decision to set up its circuit bench in Jalpaiguri. Sudip Saha said in his petition the north Bengal town lacked facilities to house 16 judges and handle cases of six districts.




